From 391945b90722b4b45fc8e8f121c52054c3fd104f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: opencode <facundovladimir@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 18:03:30 +1200
Subject: [PATCH] cmd: add `ollama voice` to talk to models with speech

Adds a local, CPU-only voice interface so users can hold a hands-free
spoken conversation with their models:

  - `ollama voice MODEL` runs a listen -> chat -> speak loop
  - `/voice` toggles speech inside the `ollama run` REPL
  - `ollama voice --setup` installs the local STT/TTS backends

The new `voice` package embeds a small Bash/Python pipeline (Silero VAD,
Parakeet STT on :5093, Supertonic TTS on :8766), extracted to
~/.ollama/voice on first use. Ollama only orchestrates the turn loop and
reuses the existing chat() round-trip; the speech backends are plain
OpenAI-compatible HTTP services configurable via STT_URL/SUPERTONIC_URL.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
